if there is already a table by this table name then will it genenrate another table by this name or enter in the same table
</user_query>"},{"role":"assistant","content":"# Room Database Table Behavior

If an entity with the same table name already exists in your Room database, it will **not** create another table with the same name. 

In your code, you have:

```kotlin
@Entity(tableName = "leetcode_users")
```

This annotation tells Room to create a table named "leetcode_users". The important behavior to understand is:

1. Room uses the table name as the unique identifier for tables in your database
2. If you have multiple entity classes with the same `tableName` value, Room will generate a build-time error
3. Room follows a "single source of truth" principle, where each table must be defined by exactly one entity class

If you need to insert data into an existing table, you'll use the DAO (Data Access Object) methods to perform those operations, but the table structure itself is defined only once in your schema.

If you're trying to modify the table structure, you'll need to handle database migrations appropriately through version changes in your Room database class."},{"role":"user","content":"<additional_data>
