I see the problem with the logout functionality. The `logout()` function in your `MainViewModel` is not correctly updating the UI state.

Here's what's happening:

```kotlin:app/src/main/java/com/devrachit/ken/presentation/screens/dashboard/ActivityContent/MainViewmodel.kt
fun logout(){
 viewModelScope.launch(Dispatchers.IO) {
 logoutUseCase()
 .collectLatest { result ->
 when (result) {
 is Resource.Loading -> {_userValues.value.copy(showDialogLoading = true)}
 is Resource.Success -> {_userValues.value.copy(showDialogLoading = true, navigateToLogin = true)}
 is Resource.Error -> {_userValues.value.copy(showDialogLoading = false)}
 }
 }
 }
}
```

## The Issue

You're creating new state objects with `copy()` but you're not actually assigning them to `_userValues.value`. You're just creating the objects and discarding them.

## Fix

Update your `logout()` function like this:

```kotlin:app/src/main/java/com/devrachit/ken/presentation/screens/dashboard/ActivityContent/MainViewmodel.kt
fun logout(){
 viewModelScope.launch(Dispatchers.IO) {
 logoutUseCase()
 .collectLatest { result ->
 when (result) {
 is Resource.Loading -> {
 _userValues.value = _userValues.value.copy(showDialogLoading = true)
 }
 is Resource.Success -> {
 _userValues.value = _userValues.value.copy(showDialogLoading = true, navigateToLogin = true)
 }
 is Resource.Error -> {
 _userValues.value = _userValues.value.copy(showDialogLoading = false)
 }
 }
 }
 }
}
```

This assigns the new state objects to `_userValues.value`, which will properly trigger the UI updates in `MainActivity.kt` where you're observing these state changes.

With this fix, the loading dialog should show when logging out, and the navigation to the login screen should happen when the logout operation succeeds."},{"role":"user","content":"<additional_data>
